@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001/api

### 1. AUTHENTICATION

### 1a. Login as 'mario' (Password is 'password' as seeded in dbSetup.js)
POST {{baseUrl}}/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "mario",
    "password": "password"
}

### 1b. Check if currently logged in
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/current

### 2. FETCHING GAME DATA (Requires Login)

### 2a. Get the full network (stations and valid segments)
GET {{baseUrl}}/network

### 2b. Get the leaderboard rankings
GET {{baseUrl}}/rankings

### 3. PLAYING THE GAME (Requires Login)

### 3a. Initialize a new game (Server picks random Start and Dest)
POST {{baseUrl}}/games/init

### 3b. Submit a route (TEST 1: PERFECT VALID ROUTE)
POST {{baseUrl}}/games/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "gameData": {
        "startStation": { "id": 1, "name": "Centrale" },
        "destStation": { "id": 4, "name": "Piazza delle Lanterne" }
    },
    "route": [1, 2, 3, 4]
}

### 3c. Submit a route (TEST 2: INVALID ROUTE)
# Submitting an invalid route (e.g., segment doesn't exist, like 1 to 8 directly)
# This should return a 422 Unprocessable Entity and 0 points.
POST {{baseUrl}}/games/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "gameData": {
        "startStation": { "id": 1, "name": "Centrale" },
        "destStation": { "id": 4, "name": "Piazza delle Lanterne" }
    },
    "route": [1, 8, 4]
}


### 4a. Logout
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/sessions/current

### 4b. Verify Logout (Should return 401 Not Authenticated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/network